msg.data:
Oracle Machine Learning Datastore in Autonomous Database

Oracle Machine Learning provides datastores to save your native R or Python objects such as ML models and lists, as well as OML4R or OML4Py proxy objects in your Oracle Database or Autonomous Database instance for use in embedded execution and access across database sessions.

Initialize interpreters for R and Python and create native model objects

paragraphs.title: Import OML4R 'ORE' package and create an in-database machine learning model
paragraphs.text:
%r

library(ORE) 
ore.sync(table = 'IRIS_R') 

glm.mod <- ore.odmGLM(Petal.Length~., IRIS_R) 
summary(glm.mod)

paragraphs.title: Import OML4Py 'oml' package and create an in-database machine learning model
paragraphs.text:
%python

import oml

IRIS_PY = oml.sync(table = "IRIS_PY")

train_x = IRIS_PY.drop('PETAL_LENGTH')
train_y = IRIS_PY['PETAL_LENGTH']

glm_mod = oml.glm("regression")
glm_mod = glm_mod.fit(train_x, train_y)
glm_mod

paragraphs.title: Create a native Python machine learning model
paragraphs.text:
%python

from sklearn import linear_model

iris = IRIS_PY.pull()

X = iris[['PETAL_WIDTH']]
y = iris[['PETAL_LENGTH']]

lm = linear_model.LinearRegression()

lm_mod = lm.fit(X, y)

print(lm_mod.intercept_, lm_mod.coef_, lm_mod.score(X, y))

%md

## Save model objects in a datastore

paragraphs.title: Save Model and Objects into datastore in R
paragraphs.text:
%r

ore.save(glm.mod, lm.mod, name = "ds-r-1", overwrite = TRUE)

list <- list(a = 1, b = TRUE, c = "hoopsa")

ore.save(list, name = "ds-r-1", append = TRUE)

paragraphs.title: Save Model and Objects into datastore in Python
paragraphs.text:
%python

oml.ds.save(objs={'glm_mod': glm_mod, 'lm_mod': lm_mod}, name="ds-py-1", overwrite=True)

dict ={'a':1, 'b': True, 'c': "hoopsa"}

oml.ds.save(objs={'list': dict}, name="ds-py-1", append=True)

%md

%md

## Grant and revoke access privileges on datastores

msg.data: Grant and revoke access privileges on datastores

paragraphs.title: Grant datastore access to a user in R
paragraphs.text:
%r

ore.save(glm.mod, 
         name = 'ds-r-glm-mod', 
         grantable = TRUE, 
         overwrite = TRUE)

ore.grant('ds-r-glm-mod', type = 'datastore', user = 'OMLUSER2')

paragraphs.title: Grant datastore access to a user in Python
paragraphs.text:
%python

oml.ds.save(objs={'glm_mod': glm_mod}, 
           name= 'ds-py-glm-mod', 
           grantable = True, 
           overwrite = True)

oml.grant(name='ds-py-glm-mod', typ='datastore', user='OMLUSER2')
